        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 2:40PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 238 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms in
the Texas panhandle 11 miles northwest of Erick and 4 miles
southwest of Texola. These storms were drifting slowly northeast.
Although the storms may remain west of the state border, strong
winds from these thunderstorms may spread into far western Beckham
County.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Texola.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
